    <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
      <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
      <p>Billy Lee Tipton, born Dorothy Lucille Tipton on December 29, 1914, was an American jazz
        musician and bandleader who lived as a man for nearly 50 years. Tipton died on January 21,
        1989.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
      <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
      <p>A group of personal and professional photographs of Billy Tipton, including one photo
        album, four 8x10", two 5x7", and loose photos from albums. The locations of these photos
        appear to be Roseburg and Medford, OR, Spokane, WA, and Reno, NV. One is labeled "At the
        Simons Home - Spokane, 1953."</p>
    </scopecontent>
